      • getMemoryManager

        public IMemoryManager getMemoryManager()
        Description copied from interface: IQueryContext
        Return the IMemoryManager which may be used to buffer data on high level data structures, such as the HTree, for this query. Each operator in the query should in general create its own child IMemoryManager. While the overall IMemoryManager context associated with a query will be released when the query terminates, operators which create child IMemoryManager contexts are responsible for releasing their IMemoryManager in a timely fashion when the operator has finished its evaluation.
        Specified by:
        getMemoryManager in interface IQueryContext
